# Why digital history is like a DIY project

There are always those moments when life seems to reflect the
lessons being discussed in class. Sometimes there is a direct
link, like when you learn about colonization, and then you hear about
the Truth and Reconciliation Commission on the news. Other times,
though, there are connections that are maybe less obvious: connections
that makes sense to you, but if you were to tell them to someone else,
